Sentencas: In this paper, the stability of the nanorod-structured La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF)-Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (GDC) composites prepared with combined methods of electrospinning and infiltration has been investigated.
Titulo: Stability of nanorod-structured La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For comparison, conventional nanoparticle-structured LSCF-GDC composite cathodes were also developed.
Titulo: Stability of nanorod-structured La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectra of these LSCF-GDC composite cathodes at open circuit potentials were measured using an electrolyte-supported LSCF-GDC/GDC/LSCF-GDC symmetric cell configuration for stability evaluation.
Titulo: Stability of nanorod-structured La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results show that the conventional LSCF-GDC composite cathode has poor stability, with its polarization resistance increasing from 0.80 to 1.37 Omega cm(2) after being polarized under a current density of 100 mA cm(-2) for 120 h at 650 degrees C.
Titulo: Stability of nanorod-structured La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This degradation is attributed to the agglomeration of cathode materials and to poor contact between the cathode and the electrolyte.
Titulo: Stability of nanorod-structured La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: hi contrast, the nanorod-structured LSCF-GDC composite cathode exhibits an excellent performance stability, since its polarization resistance decreases from 0.097 to 0.077 Omega cm(2) after polarization for 144 h under a current density as high as 300 mA cm(-2).
Titulo: Stability of nanorod-structured La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, a nearly constant polarization resistance is maintained during a 20-cycle thermo-cyclic test.
Titulo: Stability of nanorod-structured La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The outstanding stability of the nanorod-structured LSCF-GDC composite cathode is ascribed to the stability of its microstructure with continuous electronic and ionic conduction pathways and high porosity, this microstructure is realized through the suppression of LSCF agglomeration by the compact GDC layers.
Titulo: Stability of nanorod-structured La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These results demonstrate that the nanorod-structured LSCF-GDC composite is a reliable material for use as intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode with a high performance.
Titulo: Stability of nanorod-structured La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
